					<provenance>The "Pote Collection" arrived in England from India in <date calendar="#Gregorian">1790</date> and was divided between the Colleges of Eton and King's, Cambridge, with the first half alphabetically going to King's. Both halves of the collection are now housed in Cambridge University Library on permanent loan. Most if not all of the manuscripts had previously been owned by <persName key="person_7537069" role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">Colonel Antoine-Louis Henri Polier (1741–1795)</persName>.
					</provenance>
